100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 29, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing the ongoing tensions in the Far East and the need for collective security. In the United States, the Scopes Trial verdict continued to spark debates over evolution and education, reflecting deep societal divides. Meanwhile, reports from Turkey indicated further political unrest as the nation adjusted to its recent secular reforms under Mustafa Kemal Atatrk.
